quran[46]{c,v,t}:
  79,1,"By those who pull out [evil souls] harshly"
  79,2,"and by those who draw out [good souls] gently"
  79,3,and by those who glide swiftly
  79,4,and those who overtake one another as in a race
  79,5,"and those who carry out the command [of Allah]"
  79,6,"on the Day when the earth convulses [by the first Blast]"
  79,7,followed by the second Blast
  79,8,hearts will be pounding on that Day
  79,9,and their eyes will be downcast
  79,10,"They say, “Will we be brought back to life"
  79,11,after we have turned into decayed bones?”
  79,12,"They say, “Then that would surely be a losing return!”"
  79,13,It will only be a single Blast
  79,14,then they will immediately be above the ground
  79,15,Has there come to you the story of Moses
  79,16,when his Lord called out to him at the sacred valley of Tuwa
  79,17,"[Saying,] “Go to Pharaoh, for he has transgressed all bounds”"
  79,18,"And say: ‘Are you willing to be purified"
  79,19,and I will guide you to your Lord so that you may fear Him?’”
  79,20,Then Moses showed him the greatest sign
  79,21,But Pharaoh denied it and disobeyed
  79,22,Then he turned back striving to plot
  79,23,"He gathered [his people] and proclaimed"
  79,24,"saying, “I am your lord, the most high.”"
  79,25,So Allah seized him for an exemplary punishment in this life and in the Hereafter
  79,26,"Indeed, there is a lesson in this for those who fear Allah"
  79,27,Are you more difficult to create or the heaven that He built
  79,28,He raised it high and proportioned it
  79,29,and darkened its night and brought forth its daylight
  79,30,And thereafter He spread out the earth
  79,31,brought forth from it its water and its pasture
  79,32,and set the mountains firmly
  79,33,as a provision for you and your grazing livestock
  79,34,But when the Supreme Calamity comes
  79,35,on that Day man will remember all what he did
  79,36,and the Blazing Fire will be exposed for all to see
  79,37,As for those who transgressed
  79,38,and preferred the life of this world
  79,39,the Blazing Fire will be their abode
  79,40,But those who feared standing before their Lord and restrained themselves from evil desires
  79,41,Paradise will surely be their abode
  79,42,"They ask you concerning the Hour, “When will it be?”"
  79,43,How could you possibly mention that
  79,44,Its knowledge rests only with your Lord
  79,45,You are only a warner for those who fear it
  79,46,"On the Day when they see it, it will be as if they had remained [in this world] no more than an evening or a morning"